description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;An exciting opportunity is available for a Consultant Clinical Psychologist/ Psychological Therapist to join a dynamic Community Mental Health Team. Carlisle Community Mental Health Assessment and Recovery Team is based in Portland Place, Carlisle and consists of a Multi- Disciplinary team with Psychiatrists, Mental health Nurses, Social Workers, Occupational Therapists and Psychologists/ Psychological Therapists. The team works within several treatment pathways including Psychosis, Non-Psychosis and Early Intervention in Psychosis.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Psychology team currently provide a wide range of treatments including CBT, MBT, EMDR and Psychodynamic therapies. This post offers a Consultant grade Psychologist/ Psychological Therapist an opportunity to lead and develop the team with particular responsibility for the Psychosis pathway.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The new investment to improve access to psychological therapies for people with severe and enduring mental health difficulties presents excellent opportunity for the successful candidate. The fact that North Cumbria is now a fully integrated part of the very successful CNTW trust means it is possible to live in one of the most beautiful parts of the world and work in one of the best mental health providers. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Douglas Maisey&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Associate Director of Psychological Services/Consultant Clinical Psychologist&lt;/p&gt;
